    <section class="what-is-pdr">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12 heading-white">
                    <h2>We Specialize In Collision AND PDR. Why We Do Both.</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-12 text-center">
                    We started in the collision and hail repair industry as a PDR company, but have since grown into a full collision shop as well!  
<br><br>
Paintless Dent Removal, or PDR, is the art of manipulating and shaping metal to restore areas that have been damaged. We prefer to repair using the PDR technique without any form of fillers or paint whenever we have the chance. We achieve this by working on affected panels from the back side so it won’t harm the factory finish of the vehicle.
<br><br>
Unfortunately not all repairs can be achieved using PDR and that's where our expertise in collision, body shop and paint come in.  Although new to the collision repair industry, we've already grown into one of Denver's top auto body shops!  
<br><br>
Our past customers would get into an accident and immediately call us requesting a repair and for a few years we were not able to accommodate them.  The worst part, we didn't have too many places where we could send an honest referral, trusting that they would do the right thing by our customers.  So now we have a full body shop that has a frame machine, 2 paint booths, upstairs and downstairs repair facilities and partner with state of the art paint suppliers!  
<br><br>
Now when you think Front Range you don't only think hail and PDR repair, but collision repair as well!
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-12 heading-white"> 
                    <h2>The Benefits Of Combining PDR AND Traditional Body Work</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-12 text-center">          
Let's face it, we would love to have your business and repair your vehicle.  What sets us apart from other shops is that we can repair your collision damage by combining traditional body repair methods with paintless dent repair methods.<br><br>Whereas most body shops use only the means that are available to them by grinding on your metal and using Bondo or other body fillers WE are able to manipulate your collision damage with paintless dent repair methods and then get it to paint.  Through this method we are able to maintain more of your vehicle's original structure, be less invasive with our repairs and promote longevity to the repaired areas.  
                    <a href="what-is-pdr/">
                      <button class="btn cta-button cta-button-black" style="margin: 15px auto 25px" type="button">LEARN MORE</button>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section>
        <div class="container-fluid container-with-padding">
            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-xs-12">
                    <div class="row boxes-full">
                                                    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 box">
                                <img src="core/views/fd759dce0a/assets/img/whoweare-1.jpg" alt="car dent"/>
